1
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:46,440
Sir,

2
00:01:46,520 --> 00:01:48,450
your clothes have been delivered.

3
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:25,370
Good morning, Colonel Takeki.

4
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:26,240
Good morning.

5
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:29,440
This is the Chief of Staff of the Shanghai Garrison,

6
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:31,240
Major General Tangchuan Yasuo.

7
00:02:32,079 --> 00:02:34,000
This is Mr. Inoue Akira.

8
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:38,320
I am the General's adjutant.

9
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:40,500
Please come in.

10
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:44,640
Commander Sawada Shigeru has gone to Nanjing.

11
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:48,160
I heard someone from the Imperial Palace has arrived,

12
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:50,320
so I came to meet you instead.

13
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:52,050
So early in the morning.

14
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:53,980
I hope I'm not disturbing you.

15
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:54,960
Not at all.

16
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:55,920
Please, General.

17
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:56,450
Alright.

18
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:10,520
I checked the records.

19
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:13,240
We received it several days ago.

20
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:16,200
The notification from Military Command.

21
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:20,320
After Commander Takeda Shigeru approved it,

22
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:22,840
he went to Nanjing.

23
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:27,160
I overlooked you, Colonel.

24
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:30,600
That's why Inoue had

25
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:32,760
a conflict with you.

26
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,040
Wumu,

27
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:36,680
I'm really sorry.

28
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:37,960
Not at all, General.

29
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:39,160
It's fine.

30
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,440
Regarding intelligence channels,

31
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:42,300
someone's been looking after me.

32
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:46,079
It's Major Takizawa from Intelligence, isn't it?

33
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:48,400
You two were classmates, right?

34
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:49,800
Yes.

35
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:57,160
I've dreamed countless times

36
00:03:57,160 --> 00:04:00,360
about our first night together.

37
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:01,880
But now,

38
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,200
my mission

39
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:06,040
forces me to share a room

40
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:09,040
with a stranger.

41
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:18,360
You intelligence people are so tight-lipped.

42
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:21,959
Major Takizawa didn't report anything either.

43
00:04:21,959 --> 00:04:24,320
I hadn't heard a word about this.

44
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,480
I'm terribly sorry.

45
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:27,010
I asked him to keep it quiet.

46
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:47,920
I know you've come all the way to Shanghai, Colonel.

47
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:52,240
You must be carrying an important mission from His Majesty.

48
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:56,159
I shouldn't ask too many questions.

49
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:59,880
Just tell me what you need from me.

50
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:02,960
I will fully cooperate.

51
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:03,840
Very good.

52
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:08,520
How long do you plan to stay in Shanghai, Colonel?

53
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:09,840
My business in Shanghai

54
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:11,170
is basically finished.

55
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:13,360
There's a ship tonight

56
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:15,120
heading to the Sixth Air Base.

57
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:16,920
I have some matters to attend to there.

58
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,280
I would like your department

59
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:20,120
to provide me with two special passes

60
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:22,120
and the best cabin accommodations.

61
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:24,640
I'll handle this matter.

62
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:27,400
Since our intelligence department's

63
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:29,600
advisor Major Takizawa has been

64
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:32,159
secretly accompanying the envoy these days,

65
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:34,480
I'll call the military police

66
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,680
and have Major Takizawa

67
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:37,040
accompany you to handle it.

68
00:05:37,040 --> 00:05:38,000
Thank you, General.

69
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,130
I'm counting on you.

70
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,920
Colonel,

71
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,240
do you understand English?

72
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,640
A little bit.

73
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,159
I heard from my son

74
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,480
that the commander of the Sixth Air Base,

75
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,520
Mr. Fujita,

76
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,780
is also quite knowledgeable in English.

77
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:56,360
Yes.

78
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:58,960
This book is what I'm taking to the island

79
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:00,560
to give to Commander Fujita.

80
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:06,360
The book the Colonel is giving to Commander Fujita

81
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:09,440
must be quite insightful.

82
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:12,280
May I borrow it for a read?

83
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:13,800
Of course.

84
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:14,600
You may.

85
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:29,400
It seems Commander Fujita is quite knowledgeable.

86
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:31,680
Yes.

87
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:36,200
I'll go buy a copy myself the day after tomorrow.

88
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:40,159
Such a good book.

89
00:06:40,159 --> 00:06:42,880
May I have a look at it?

90
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:52,400
Please.

91
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,240
Inoue,

92
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:11,680
do you really understand it?

93
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:15,360
The words on this page know me,

94
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,960
but I don't know them.

95
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:21,960
I have a subordinate who can read English.

96
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:23,800
Can he read it to me?

97
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:28,200
What's written on this paper?

98
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:28,800
Wait.

99
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,400
Just a moment.

100
00:07:33,159 --> 00:07:35,000
I was reading this book last night.

101
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,680
I just happened to be on this page.

102
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,400
I was afraid I'd forget,

103
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:38,400
so I took a piece of paper

104
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:39,640
and placed it here

105
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:41,680
to make it easier to continue reading next time.

106
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:42,880
Inoue.

107
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:44,120
If you'd like to read it, please go ahead.

108
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:46,800
When I return to Shanghai next time,

109
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,200
I'll come get it from you.

110
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,000
No, that won't be necessary.

111
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,520
This is something you're giving to Commander Fujita.

112
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:54,980
How dare I take what belongs to someone else.

113
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:57,800
Colonel.

114
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:58,400
Yes, sir.

115
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,280
Tonight,

116
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:01,480
on behalf of

117
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:03,280
Commander Zeda Shigeru of the Shanghai Garrison, I'd like to host a dinner

118
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:04,810
to entertain you, Colonel,

119
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:07,240
as a gesture of hospitality.

120
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:08,370
Thank you, General.

121
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:10,400
However, tonight

122
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,040
I've already arranged to meet an important client.

123
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,160
And tonight I'll be taking a boat

124
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,440
to the 6th Naval Base.

125
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,200
So,

126
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:16,520
wait until next time.

127
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:18,160
When I return,

128
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:20,440
we'll drink to our heart's content.

129
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,680
That works too.

130
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:25,600
By then, Commander Sawada Shigeru

131
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,530
should be back in Shanghai as well.

132
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:28,960
Inoue,

133
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,320
I'm leaving tonight.

134
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:33,159
Please tell your men to stop following me,

135
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:33,960
would you?

136
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,280
Inoue,

137
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:39,799
if this is happening,

138
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:41,780
it absolutely must not continue.

139
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:43,360
I understand.

140
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:54,960
Come out.

141
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,040
They're gone.

142
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:09,610
That really scared me to death.

143
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,280
I'm sorry.

144
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:33,240
What is this?

145
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,280
What gives you the right to enter my room?

146
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:38,610
Getting to know each other, like you said.

147
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,900
Where's the original one?

148
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:41,680
I threw it away.

149
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:43,210
Flushed it down the toilet.

150
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:44,560
So...

151
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,000
You've seen it.

152
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:47,360
Childish.

153
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:50,760
That's my property.

154
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:51,640
How dare you take it without permission?

155
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:53,520
Didn't your supervisor tell you before you came?

156
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:54,000
That nothing

157
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,160
should be recorded in written form.

158
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:56,490
Did they tell you or not?

159
00:09:56,640 --> 00:09:57,640
Didn't your supervisor tell you

160
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:59,800
not to take other people's belongings?

161
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:00,280
So...

162
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:03,290
Mine.

163
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,660
What are you doing?

164
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:05,400
[Flushing]

165
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:05,840
What are you doing?

166
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:06,320
Give it back to me.

167
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:07,240
That's me sleeping.

168
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,640
You can't show it to anyone.

169
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:09,640
Give it back to me!

170
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:13,240
Wumu Yilang.

171
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:15,120
Did you return

172
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:18,960
my things?

173
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:22,410
Getting dressed and going out.

174
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:35,280
Any progress with the envoy?

175
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:36,960
Major Ferguson

176
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:38,760
has arrived at our base in India.

177
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:42,040
But after Japan invaded Burma,

178
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,800
all air and ground routes were cut off.

179
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:44,680
Once the new routes are ready,

180
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,040
we can prepare to depart.

181
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:48,040
The situation is becoming clearer.

182
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:49,720
Damn Himalayas.

183
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:53,060
I don't know how planes can fly over them.

184
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:53,400
Sir,

185
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:55,400
trust our pilots.

186
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:57,280
I'll definitely figure out a way.

187
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:58,400
Speaking of pilots,

188
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:00,240
how are Doolittle and the boys doing?

189
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,800
Colonel Doolittle and his men are preparing

190
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,930
to launch B-25s from the carrier deck.

191
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,840
Tomorrow they'll fly to Sacramento

192
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:07,100
for further training.

193
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,280
Tell Doolittle

194
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:09,640
this operation must be foolproof.

195
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:12,600
The Japanese are about to take the Philippines.

196
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:15,600
I want this raid to happen as soon as possible.

197
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:16,640
Call him right now.

198
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:17,170
Yes, sir.

199
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:21,880
Sir,

200
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:23,920
we've made the following necessary modifications:

201
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,600
Removed the belly turret

202
00:11:25,640 --> 00:11:28,040
and replaced it with a 50-gallon fuel tank.

203
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:30,400
Added four auxiliary fuel tanks

204
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:32,160
bringing each aircraft's fuel capacity

205
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:34,200
to 1,141 gallons.

206
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,400
Modified the bombsights

207
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:38,400
for low-altitude bombing.

208
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:42,040
A small camera has been installed in the tail of the aircraft.

209
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:44,240
Many radio devices have been removed

210
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:45,960
to reduce weight.

211
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:48,040
De-icers have also been installed on the wings,

212
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:48,570
correct?

213
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:51,880
Okay, and finally...

214
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,200
Finally what?

215
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,280
The tail gun has been

216
00:11:58,640 --> 00:12:01,600
replaced with a painted wooden stick.

217
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:04,080
As per your orders, sir.

218
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:07,240
Tow the aircraft to the test runway.

219
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:13,970
Colonel, is that really a broomstick?

220
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,040
Have I ever told you

221
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:16,600
about my father's hobbies?

222
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:18,600
Carpenter.

223
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,720
Just like Jesus Christ and the Savior.

224
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,520
My father could make

225
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:24,960
rifles out of wood with more firepower than a machine gun.

226
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:25,720
Trust me.

227
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:28,040
I know what I'm going to do with this thing.

228
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:28,640
Yes, sir.

229
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:30,320
In case my plane

230
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:30,920
runs into Hitler's aircraft,

231
00:12:30,920 --> 00:12:33,050
I'll just poke it down with that stick.

232
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:35,650
Get this one ready for takeoff.

233
00:12:41,040 --> 00:12:43,520
7701 taxiing to runway.

234
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:45,720
7701 cleared for test flight.

235
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:49,800
7702 taxiing to runway.

236
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:50,800
Copy that.

237
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:57,160
7701 test flight on 250-meter runway.

238
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:58,160
Understood.

239
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,440
Is it still because the aircraft is too heavy?

240
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:32,040
No problem. Let's try again.

241
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:37,560
7702, test flight on 250-meter runway.

242
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:38,560
7702 copy that.

243
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:40,240
Cole.

244
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:43,160
Remember what I taught you.

245
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:45,320
Keep the flaps down.

246
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,880
Pull back on the stick.

247
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,600
Don't fall back into your old habits.

248
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:52,520
Yes, sir.

249
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:56,480
Flaps down.

250
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:14,900
Full throttle.

251
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:16,010
Throttle

252
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:26,840
ready.

253
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:44,960
Come on, baby, lift off!

254
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:55,040
We made it!

255
00:14:58,360 --> 00:14:59,360
That was awesome!

256
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:01,760
We did it!

257
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,600
7702.

258
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:16,320
Successfully took off from a 250-meter runway.

259
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:19,480
Congratulations.

260
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:31,520
Prepare the next aircraft. Get everything ready.

261
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:31,840
Sir.

262
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:32,520
Sir.

263
00:15:33,040 --> 00:15:33,440
Sir.

264
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:36,560
The machine guns on the other planes haven't been removed yet.

265
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:37,960
What are you waiting for?

266
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:41,280
You're right.

267
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:45,840
Boys, you've seen Cole's performance.

268
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:48,600
All planes should take off according to this standard.

269
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:49,440
Let's do it.

270
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:22,240
Thank you.

271
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:37,440
We will be leaving later today

272
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:39,560
on the Japanese transport ship Amemaru

273
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:41,290
from Huangpu Port in Shanghai.

274
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:42,840
It's a journey of one day and two nights.

275
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,960
We should arrive around 5 a.m. the day after tomorrow

276
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:46,080
at Sanzao Island

277
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:47,680
at the Navy's Sixth Air Base.

278
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:50,640
That's great!

279
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:52,420
We can finally go home.

280
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:54,200
Takizawa has figured out

281
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,560
the situation on the ship.

282
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:57,280
They're mostly Japanese soldiers.

283
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:58,680
There are only two Chinese people.

284
00:16:58,680 --> 00:17:00,800
One is Commander Fujita's translator from the island.

285
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:02,130
And the other one is you.

286
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:08,040
By the way,

287
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:09,520
that book you gave me,

288
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:10,400
I think

289
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,530
I found the part you're interested in.

290
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:13,690
Tell me about it.

291
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:15,400
The author, Homan Lai,

292
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:18,000
