293
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:18,640
He said

294
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:20,359
Japan would launch surprise attacks on

295
00:17:20,359 --> 00:17:21,560
Pearl Harbor naval base,

296
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:23,200
Guam and the Philippines.

297
00:17:23,560 --> 00:17:24,160
The route would be

298
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:25,760
the northern Pacific route.

299
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:28,800
Isn't that the same route

300
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:30,730
Japan used to attack Pearl Harbor?

301
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:33,680
I remember he wrote in this book that

302
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,760
early Sunday morning,

303
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:37,360
the US Pacific Fleet's

304
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,400
home base at Pearl Harbor,

305
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:40,200
200 nautical miles to the north,

306
00:17:40,280 --> 00:17:42,880
the eastern horizon was beginning to lighten,

307
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:45,360
the peaceful dawn was approaching.

308
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:47,240
A massive fleet

309
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:49,520
along a route never used by merchant ships,

310
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:50,760
the northern Pacific route,

311
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:51,720
breaking the silence

312
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:53,800
gradually heading south toward Pearl Harbor.

313
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,160
This massive fleet

314
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:57,160
consisted of aircraft carriers

315
00:17:57,520 --> 00:17:59,440
arranged in two columns as the main formation.

316
00:17:59,440 --> 00:18:02,200
Several fast battleships at each corner

317
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:03,680
and heavy cruisers.

318
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:06,520
Destroyers formed the outer perimeter.

319
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:09,040
And in front of this ring of steel,

320
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:11,680
leading the way were several light cruisers

321
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:12,800
and submarines.

322
00:18:13,280 --> 00:18:15,440
On the deck of each aircraft carrier

323
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:17,400
were rows of planes with wings spread

324
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:19,880
and engines running.

325
00:18:20,280 --> 00:18:22,040
Hanging beneath their fuselages were

326
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:24,240
either heavy bombs or torpedoes.

327
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:26,440
The lead-gray torpedo casings

328
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:27,900
gleamed with a cold light.

329
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,000
What's wrong?

330
00:18:32,360 --> 00:18:34,890
You memorized all that after reading it once?

331
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:41,440
This amazing American writer

332
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:43,880
accurately predicted in his book

333
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:44,640
a few months ago,

334
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:46,480
the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbor

335
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:47,880
with complete accuracy.

336
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:49,680
When was this book published?

337
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:50,520
1925.

338
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:52,240
1925.

339
00:18:54,080 --> 00:18:56,040
At that time, Yamamoto Isoroku

340
00:18:56,480 --> 00:18:58,800
was a military attaché at the Washington embassy.

341
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:02,320
Fujita was an assistant military attaché at the New York consulate.

342
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:03,280
I believe Yamamoto

343
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:04,680
must have read this book.

344
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:05,560
Now I understand

345
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:07,440
why Fujita has been looking for this book.

346
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:08,160
He wants to find

347
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:09,820
Yamamoto's line of thinking.

348
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:11,900
These high-ranking officers

349
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:14,690
aren't interested in martial arts displays.

350
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:16,520
I've been searching for a key

351
00:19:16,760 --> 00:19:18,020
to unlock their minds.

352
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:20,880
You've helped me find it.

353
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:23,970
I've done something great!

354
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:42,160
Sorry to disturb your meal.

355
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:42,920
Go ahead.

356
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:44,920
Sanzao Island sent a telegram.

357
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:48,040
The day after tomorrow morning,

358
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:50,480
