The Japanese military hierarchy is strict.

370
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:14,800
If a high-ranking officer refused

371
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,880
this mere two-hour flight,

372
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:18,320
and chose for himself and his female companion

373
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:20,760
to drift at sea for two nights and a day instead,

374
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:22,080
it would quickly raise

375
00:20:22,320 --> 00:20:24,320
Major General Tangchuan Anfu's suspicions.

376
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:25,640
Please thank the General for me,

377
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:26,800
and inform him that

378
00:20:27,080 --> 00:20:28,440
I will take the plane,

379
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:29,680
while my girlfriend will travel by boat.

380
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:30,520
Yes, sir.

381
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:31,000
Thank you.

382
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,260
I'll take my leave now.

383
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,120
What's wrong?

384
00:20:49,960 --> 00:20:50,920
It's me, Wumu.

385
00:20:51,920 --> 00:20:53,650
There's been a change of plans.

386
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:54,800
Tang Anchuanfu's deputy

387
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:55,680
came to see me

388
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:56,680
and said that the day after tomorrow morning,

389
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:58,940
there's a plane flying to Sanzao Island.

390
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:00,240
This means

391
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:03,220
Miss Ye will have to take the boat by herself.

392
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:05,000
The question is whether it's safe.

393
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,800
There shouldn't be any problem,

394
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:08,640
but we need to make proper arrangements.

395
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:09,440
I understand.

396
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:17,440
I have to go alone, right?

397
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:22,360
Takizawa and I will arrange for you to board the ship.

398
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:23,280
The ship

399
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:25,480
is full of Japanese soldiers.

400
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:27,240
Besides the Japanese soldiers,

401
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:28,880
there are also some non-combatants,

402
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:31,540
but they're all connected to the Sixth Air Base.

403
00:21:31,560 --> 00:21:32,960
Takizawa and I will make arrangements.

404
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:34,490
They won't dare to harm you.

405
00:21:36,160 --> 00:21:36,640
Okay.

406
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:41,200
So...

407
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:43,640
I want to freshen up.

408
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:46,680
I don't want to see my father like this.

409
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:47,040
Okay.

410
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:50,460
No matter who you meet on the ship,

411
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:52,640
don't discuss politics.

412
00:21:53,760 --> 00:21:54,820
Whatever happens,

413
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:56,800
remember to stay silent.

414
00:21:57,360 --> 00:22:00,020
I'll arrive on the island only 5 hours after you.

415
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:04,840
Also,

416
00:22:21,360 --> 00:22:22,960
there's a special situation

417
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:25,540
I feel I need to tell you about.

418
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:27,800
If anything goes wrong

419
00:22:28,520 --> 00:22:30,800
and you fall into the hands of the Japanese military police,

420
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:32,520
their typical interrogation method

421
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:34,920
is to first bring in a hot-tempered officer.

422
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:35,780
He will beat you

423
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:36,800
and insult you.

424
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:37,600
Threaten you.

425
00:22:37,960 --> 00:22:39,960
Make you feel extremely terrified.

426
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:42,000
Just when you're on the verge of breaking down,

427
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:44,000
an officer of higher rank will appear,

428
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,860
but with a much gentler attitude.

429
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:47,840
He will be very friendly to you.

430
00:22:47,840 --> 00:22:49,370
You'll feel grateful to him

431
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:50,760
and involuntarily tell him

432
00:22:50,760 --> 00:22:51,960
everything you know.

433
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,730
Especially at that moment,

434
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:56,940
remember, you must hold firm.

435
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:01,600
So

436
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:03,680
I might get arrested.

437
00:23:20,560 --> 00:23:23,040
I understand. You may go.

438
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,000
Let's go back.

439
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:30,100
We're making no progress here at all.

440
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:32,560
That's impossible.

441
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:34,530
Should we search again?

442
00:23:34,560 --> 00:23:35,280
No need.

443
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:37,400
All units can return to base.

444
00:23:42,080 --> 00:23:44,520
Let's check with the coastal defense unit

445
00:23:44,520 --> 00:23:47,080
and see if their search yielded anything.

446
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:49,930
First squad, follow me.

447
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:58,400
Sasaki,

448
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:01,800
tell Tang Bingchen, the chairman of the maintenance association,

449
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:03,640
to come to my office.

450
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:05,610
Should we search underground?

451
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:08,240
About face! Forward march!

452
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:11,240
This isn't over yet.

453
00:24:45,240 --> 00:24:45,720
Ju'er.

454
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:48,160
How did you get in here?

455
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:49,800
If the Japanese find out, we're done for.

456
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:52,320
Why couldn't you come to my house if you needed something?

457
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:53,320
I won't go to your house.

458
00:24:53,320 --> 00:24:55,080
I'm afraid I can't control my temper.

459
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:55,800
I am who I am.

460
00:24:56,520 --> 00:24:57,760
My father is who he is.

461
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:00,040
Ju'er.

462
00:25:00,160 --> 00:25:02,040
It's not that I'm afraid to go to your house.

463
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:03,640
What if I get into an argument with your father?

464
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:05,300
That would be awkward for you.

465
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:07,400
Anyway, let's not talk about this.

466
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:08,720
I came to see you for something.

467
00:25:08,720 --> 00:25:11,720
Where does your hospital usually keep the medicines?

468
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:13,820
Why are you asking about this?

469
00:25:15,720 --> 00:25:16,200
Well...

470
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:18,680
My mother-in-law accidentally cut her arm.

471
00:25:18,680 --> 00:25:19,240
I want to get her some medicine.

472
00:25:19,240 --> 00:25:20,640
Your mother-in-law is hurt?

473
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:21,440
Is it serious?

474
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:23,640
I could come by after work to check on her.

475
00:25:23,640 --> 00:25:24,240
No, no.

476
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:24,680
That's not necessary.

477
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:26,000
It's not serious.

478
00:25:26,720 --> 00:25:29,120
I just want to find some penicillin for her.

479
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:31,160
Just stop asking so many questions.

480
00:25:31,160 --> 00:25:33,480
Just tell me where your pharmacy is.

481
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:35,760
Even if I tell you where it is,

482
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:37,290
you won't be able to get any.

483
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:39,330
All those medicines are locked up.

484
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:42,240
What should I do then?

485
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:43,100
How about this.

486
00:25:44,760 --> 00:25:46,480
I'll go to the comfort station

487
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:47,680
for routine inspection

488
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:49,210
and try to get you two doses.

489
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:50,060
Really?

490
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:51,360
That's great.

491
00:25:52,360 --> 00:25:53,880
Is it dangerous?

492
00:25:55,040 --> 00:25:56,370
Don't worry. It's fine.

493
00:25:57,640 --> 00:25:58,640
That's good then.

494
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:00,200
I'll go now.

495
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:01,200
Be careful.

496
00:26:01,240 --> 00:26:02,200
Okay, bye.

497
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:25,960
[Chong 59362]

498
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:33,080
Everything is arranged.

499
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:34,720
When we arrive at the dock,

500
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:36,480
I'll call the captain over

501
00:26:36,840 --> 00:26:38,300
so you can meet each other.

502
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:39,210
Don't worry.

503
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:40,840
He's quite timid.

504
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:44,810
The captain is from Kyushu.

505
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:46,240
When we get there,

506
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:47,200
I'll instruct him

507
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:48,460
to ensure your safety.

508
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:50,940
Give me your gun first.

509
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:53,960
What do you need my gun for?

510
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:55,080
When we get to the dock,

511
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:56,280
I'll give you the gun

512
00:26:56,400 --> 00:26:57,600
in front of everyone,

513
00:26:57,720 --> 00:27:00,520
so they know you have a weapon to protect yourself.

514
00:27:13,360 --> 00:27:14,240
Can I

515
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:17,960
stop by the department store?

516
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:20,850
There's still time.

517
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:23,620
What do you need to buy?

518
00:27:25,760 --> 00:27:27,820
Something unrelated to the mission.

519
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:30,530
I'm going to buy glasses for my dad.

520
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:32,920
Let's go.

521
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:47,780
You need to hug me before we leave.

522
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:48,360
What?

523
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:49,330
Colonel.

524
00:27:51,800 --> 00:27:52,330
Captain.

525
00:27:52,840 --> 00:27:53,960
This is our Colonel.

526
00:27:53,960 --> 00:27:54,520
Colonel.

527
00:28:01,560 --> 00:28:03,020
Take good care of my woman.

528
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:04,840
If anything happens to her,

529
00:28:04,840 --> 00:28:06,440
no matter where you go,

530
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:07,480
I will find you.

531
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:09,160
Yes, Colonel.

532
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:11,860
Keep this with you.

533
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:13,640
If anything unexpected happens,

534
00:28:13,640 --> 00:28:15,300
use this to protect yourself.

535
00:28:33,800 --> 00:28:34,560
Go now.

536
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:05,160
Let's go.

537
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:06,920
Don't be so reluctant.

538
00:29:49,080 --> 00:29:50,720
Is this your cabin?

539
00:29:54,280 --> 00:29:56,760
The best cabin on this ship.

540
00:29:58,040 --> 00:30:00,760
Shanghai authorities strictly ordered me

541
00:30:00,760 --> 00:30:01,960
to give it up.

542
00:30:02,720 --> 00:30:03,720
I thought

543
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:06,400
some important figure was coming,

544
00:30:06,440 --> 00:30:07,280
but it turns out to be

545
00:30:07,280 --> 00:30:08,680
a Chinese woman.

546
00:30:13,320 --> 00:30:14,560
My name is Fukuda.

547
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:18,000
All the supplies for the Sixth Air Base

548
00:30:18,560 --> 00:30:20,400
are brought by me.

549
00:30:21,680 --> 00:30:24,720
If you need money on the island, you can come to me.

550
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:27,040
I also have a

551
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:29,770
workplace specifically for women on the island.

552
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:31,120
By the way,

553
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:33,620
you can also come to me if you don't have a job.

554
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:36,320
I don't need a job,

555
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:37,570
and I don't know you.

556
00:30:37,880 --> 00:30:39,210
Would you please leave?

557
00:30:40,120 --> 00:30:40,920
Mr. Fukuda,

558
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:43,280
what brings you here?

559
00:30:43,280 --> 00:30:44,610
I'm not looking for you.

560
00:30:45,040 --> 00:30:46,280
I'm looking for the captain.

561
00:30:46,280 --> 00:30:48,010
You're all brainless animals.

562
00:30:51,520 --> 00:30:52,520
Don't mind him.

563
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:54,120
This man is Fukuda.

564
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:56,420
He's a very unpleasant Japanese man.

565
00:30:56,520 --> 00:30:58,000
The place he just mentioned

566
00:30:58,000 --> 00:30:59,400
that offers jobs to women

567
00:30:59,680 --> 00:31:02,610
is actually a comfort station for the Imperial Army.

568
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:06,340
My name is Luo Zhiyong.

569
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:07,760
I work at the Sixth Aviation Base

570
00:31:07,760 --> 00:31:09,680
as Commander Fujita's translator.

571
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:10,840
I am Chinese.

572
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:15,360
I'm Ye Biying.

573
00:31:16,120 --> 00:31:17,720
If I'm not mistaken,

574
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:20,800
this is the first time a Chinese woman has appeared on this ship.

575
00:31:20,800 --> 00:31:21,440
And

